The paper deals with complexity and algorithms for a graph problem, specifically the Small-Set Expansion problem. This suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The use of random walks and adjacency matrices suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on gap amplification and soundness/completeness parameters suggests a connection to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
